<p>[On letterhead of the British Red Cross and Order of St. John.]<br/>13/7/18</p>
<p>Dear Miss King</p>
<p>Am dropping you these few lines letting you know I am still in the land of the living. I think I wrote before and told you I were in Hospital with gas burns but have now been discharged to a convalesent camp.</p>
<p>It is run by the BRCS [British Red Cross Society] and it is a fine</p>
